Flight cancellations soared by 20 per cent and delays by 7 per cent in the first quarter of 2015 .
In the first four months of the year , there have so far been 5,080 flight cancellations , compared to 4,239 cancellations during the same period in 2014 .
The number of delays also increased to 2,427 from 2,260 in 2015 .
And airlines are refuting the figures .